All Progressives Congress (APC) Governors under the aegis of the Progressive Governors Forum (PGF) have eulogised the contributions of Senator Oluremi Tinubu to the democratic development of the country. They described her as a political unifying and rallying point to all. The Governors also celebrated and acknowledged the visionary leadership virtues of Senator Owelle Rochas Okorocha. The forum in a statement by its chairman, Governor Abubakar Bagudu eulogised the two leaders who celebrated their 60th and 58th birthdays respectively. They acknowledged Tinubu’s immense contributions to the country’s democratic struggles, describing her as the unifying and rallying point for all. The forum also celebrated with the national leader of the party, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, and the entire family on their matriarch’s birthday. According to them: “We acknowledge her contributions to our democratic struggles through her insightful inputs to the processes of party formation and party building as well as within the Senate Chamber. She certainly represents a unifying and rallying point for all. “Congratulations and happy 60th Birthday to Senator Oluremi Tinubu, the wife of Jagaban of the Borgu Kingdom.” Also congratulating Okorocha, they said: “We in particular wish to acknowledge and commend your leadership, vision, and commitment to a united prosperous Nigeria. “Under the leadership of our party, APC, we acknowledge your contributions to our team of Progressive Governors as a founding member of the Forum and Chairman between November 2013 – May 2019. “We also recognise your insightful and resolute inputs to the processes of managing legislation at the Senate Chamber. Congratulations and Happy Birthday to Senator Owelle Rochas Okorocha.”